# Godot Development Best Practices

## Variable and Function Declarations

- Always use typed variables with `:=` instead of `=` for better type safety
  - `var speed := 10` instead of `var speed = 10`
  - `var velocity := Vector2.ZERO` instead of `var velocity = Vector2.ZERO`
- Prefix private functions and variables with underscore `_` to denote them as private
  - `var _rotation_velocity := 0.0`
  - `func _shoot():`

## Code Structure and Flow Control

- Avoid deep nesting by using early returns and inverted conditions
  - Instead of nested if statements, use early returns when possible
  - Extract complex logic into separate functions for clarity
- Remove trailing whitespace and unnecessary brackets for cleaner code

## Input Handling

- Create custom input actions instead of using built-in UI actions
  - Define actions in Project Settings > Input Map
  - Use `Input.is_action_pressed("shoot")` instead of `Input.is_action_pressed("ui_accept")`
- Use `Input.get_axis()` for directional input handling instead of manual input processing
  - `Input.get_axis("left", "right")` for horizontal movement
  - `Input.get_axis("up", "down")` for vertical movement
## Node Management and References

- Use proper typing for instantiated nodes
  - Define custom types in scripts: `class_name Bullet`
  - Type instantiated nodes: `var bullet: Bullet = bullet_scene.instantiate()`
- Use unique names for node references to make them more robust
  - Set nodes as unique names using `%` prefix
  - Access with `%AnimatedSprite2D` instead of `$AnimatedSprite2D`
- Use groups instead of assuming parent-child relationships for safer node access
  - `get_tree().get_first_node_in_group("particle_manager")` instead of `get_parent().get_node("ParticleManager")`

## Built-in Functions and Utilities

- Use built-in Godot functions instead of manual calculations
  - `Vector2.from_angle(rotation)` instead of `Vector2(cos(rotation), sin(rotation))`
- Leverage GDScript's built-in methods for common operations

## Signal and Method Naming

- Use descriptive names for signal callback methods
  - `_on_area_2d_entered()` instead of generic names
- Make method names explicit about their purpose
  - `_shoot()` clearly indicates the method's function

## Safety and Maintainability

- Don't make assumptions about parent node structure
- Use singletons, signals, or groups for cross-node communication
- Keep code modular and functions focused on single responsibilities
- Always type your variables and function parameters for better IntelliSense and error prevention
